Package: noetica
Version: 0.4.11
Section: net
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: SourceOS Linux <maintainers@sourceos.ai>
Depends: libc6
Recommends: ollama, nodejs (>= 20)
Homepage: https://github.com/SocioProphet/Noetica
Description: Noetica agent-machine — self-hosted AI dialogue backend service
 Noetica's agent-machine is a 22-intent AI dialogue management service
 for local, sovereign AI inference. Listens on NOETICA_AM_PORT (default
 8080). Ships as a self-contained binary (no Node runtime required); a
 Node-based fallback uses nodejs (>= 20).
 .
 Requires a running Ollama instance (OLLAMA_HOST, default
 http://127.0.0.1:11434) for inference: install ollama and run
 `ollama serve`.
 .
 Integrates with TurtleTerm co-pilot as the local AI backend:
 set SOURCEOS_NOETICA_URL=http://localhost:8080
 .
 Intents: chat, explain, fix, search, summarize, translate, codegen,
 debug, refactor, test, document, deploy, review, plan, recall,
 memorize, learn, compare, analyze, classify, generate, complete.
